   "metadata": {
    "id": "7ac7f099-4bae-4fa6-bf47-a13d511cbe3e"
   },
   "source": [
    "Time-Series Extraction for VAE"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "10",
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "9676e777-1b97-4094-a4b2-efddd6a85273",
    "outputId": "0ebc92d4-ffdf-4408-ecbd-bdb3b05e181f"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Sort merged DF by date first\n",
    "df_merged_sorted = df_merged.sort('date')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Group for time-series (agg collects sorted values/dates per group)\n",
    "ts_data = df_merged_sorted.group_by(['cik', 'tag', 'name']).agg([\n",
    "    pl.col('value').cast(pl.Float64).alias('values'),\n",
    "    pl.col('date').alias('dates')\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Time-series groups shape:\", ts_data.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Sample (first row):\", ts_data.row(0))  # cik, tag, name, values list, dates list"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "11",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "66aa29ff-1b5c-4599-b909-7967d96424b3"
   },
   "source": [
    "285,275 company-metric combinations are now ready for the VAE to learn from. Previously you had only 500 — now you have 570x more data. This is a genuine upgrade.\n",
    "The sample row shows a real example:\n",
    "\n",
    "# Company: Gibraltar Industries Inc.\n",
    "\n",
    "Metric being tracked: earnings per share from discontinued operations\n",
    "Values over 3 quarters: $0.01 → $0.07 → -$0.12\n",
    "That last number going negative is exactly the kind of pattern your VAE will learn to flag — a company that was profitable, then suddenly lost money"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "12",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "b6fda218-8f21-4856-a314-78a8519eb385"
   },
   "source": [
    "Step 4: normalize/pad sequences and train VAE for anomalies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "13",
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "ec93a4c5-7acf-40bc-8232-8413d7b3995e",
    "outputId": "edd3edf3-3b21-43a3-b5a1-0dea683e5e8a"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "values_lists = ts_data['values'].to_list()\n",
    "max_len = 20\n",
    "padded_data = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for seq in values_lists:\n",
    "    if len(seq) > 0:\n",
    "        arr = np.array(seq, dtype=float)\n",
    "        # Trim to max_len first, then normalize\n",
    "        arr = arr[:max_len]\n",
    "        if arr.max() != arr.min():\n",
    "            scaled = MinMaxScaler().fit_transform(arr.reshape(-1, 1)).flatten()\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            scaled = np.zeros(len(arr))\n",
    "        # Pad if shorter than max_len\n",
    "        pad_width = max_len - len(scaled)\n",
    "        padded = np.pad(scaled, (0, pad_width), 'constant')\n",
    "        padded_data.append(padded)\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        padded_data.append(np.zeros(max_len))\n",
    "\n",
    "padded_data = np.array(padded_data)\n",
    "print(\"Padded shape:\", padded_data.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "14",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "c20618df-ec7e-4e42-8c32-fb28c9cf098d"
   },
   "source": [
    "Prepared 285,275 real financial time-series from SEC filings across 6 quarters (2024q4 to 2026q1), normalized and zero-padded to length 20, ready for VAE anomaly detection at production scale."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "15",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "f8f24720-fe99-496d-b422-abbe72ac5225"
   },
   "source": [
    "Train VAE"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "16",
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "7c56257a-48b9-4ad8-b67d-a0f801f27f17",
    "outputId": "cb790a54-68b2-4711-f07a-b3f304604cfe"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader, TensorDataset\n",
    "\n",
    "class VAE(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, seq_len=20, latent_dim=10):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.encoder = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(seq_len, 32), nn.ReLU(), nn.Linear(32, latent_dim * 2))\n",
    "        self.decoder = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(latent_dim, 32), nn.ReLU(), nn.Linear(32, seq_len), nn.Sigmoid())\n",
    "\n",
    "    def reparameterize(self, mu, logvar):\n",
    "        std = torch.exp(0.5 * logvar)\n",
    "        eps = torch.randn_like(std)\n",
    "        return mu + eps * std\n",
    "\n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        h = self.encoder(x)\n",
    "        mu, logvar = h.chunk(2, 1)\n",
    "        z = self.reparameterize(mu, logvar)\n",
    "        recon = self.decoder(z)\n",
    "        return recon, mu, logvar\n",
    "\n",
    "def loss_fn(recon, x, mu, logvar):\n",
    "    recon_loss = nn.MSELoss(reduction='sum')(recon, x)\n",
    "    kl_loss = -0.5 * torch.sum(1 + logvar - mu.pow(2) - logvar.exp())\n",
    "    return recon_loss + kl_loss\n",
    "\n",
    "# Data\n",
    "dataset = TensorDataset(torch.FloatTensor(padded_data))\n",
    "loader = DataLoader(dataset, batch_size=64, shuffle=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "model = VAE()\n",
    "optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)\n",
    "\n",
    "for epoch in range(20):\n",
    "    total_loss = 0\n",
    "    for batch in loader:\n",
    "        x = batch[0]\n",
    "        recon, mu, logvar = model(x)\n",
    "        loss = loss_fn(recon, x, mu, logvar)\n",
    "        optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "        loss.backward()\n",
    "        optimizer.step()\n",
    "        total_loss += loss.item()\n",
    "    print(f'Epoch {epoch}: Loss {total_loss / len(loader):.4f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Anomalies\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    recon, _, _ = model(torch.FloatTensor(padded_data))\n",
    "    errors = torch.mean((recon - torch.FloatTensor(padded_data)) ** 2, dim=1).numpy()\n",
    "threshold = np.percentile(errors, 95)\n",
    "anomalies = errors > threshold\n",
    "print(f\"Anomalies detected: {sum(anomalies)} ({sum(anomalies)/len(anomalies)*100:.1f}%)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "torch.save(model.state_dict(), '/content/drive/MyDrive/anomaly-detection/vae_model.pt')\n",
    "print(\"Model saved to Drive\")"
   ]
  },
